- taking into account critical issues (as in ZUIP) during the selection of themes for the cycle composition;
- ability to theoretically and critically deal with approaches to text selection for the cycle composition; and
- critical understanding of the process-approach during the teaching of an additional language.

On completion of this module the student should be able to demonstrate: 
-understanding of contested knowledge and skills for the application of various models and frameworks for the effective teaching and learning of mathematics and mathematical concepts in young 
children (birth – 4); 
-integrated knowledge and understanding of and the ability to apply the foundational perspectives; number sense, number concept and number development; patterns and functions, sorting and 
classification, spatial orientation and spatial insight as well a comparison and measurement in the early years; 
