design retrenchment policies;
analyse industrial actions; and
develop recognition agreements.

After completion of the module, the student should be able to:
define different SHRM strategies;
identify an appropriate HRM strategy in enhancing organisational performance;
demonstrate the understanding of HRM strategies;
describe different strategies to be applied in different HR functions;
analyse the vision, mission and objectives of an organisation;
prepare a human resource plan in line with the chosen strategy;
modify the vision and mission of the organisation in order to suit its objectives;
